Sentencas: 10 mol% gadolinium doped ceria (GDC10) is widely used as a barrier layer between oxygen electrode and electrolyte to prevent interfacial reactions.
Titulo: Heavily neodymium doped ceria as an effective barrier layer in solid oxide electrochemical cells

Sentencas: A 50 mol% neodymium doped ceria (NDC50) barrier layer has been proposed and studied in this paper.
Titulo: Heavily neodymium doped ceria as an effective barrier layer in solid oxide electrochemical cells

Sentencas: Symmetrical cells with NDC50 and GDC10 barrier layers, Nd2NiO4+delta(NNO)eCe(0.5)Nd(0.5)O(2-delta)(NDC50) electrode, and YSZ electrolyte have been systematically studied using impedance spectroscopy (EIS) at various temperatures and oxygen partial pressure (pO(2)).
Titulo: Heavily neodymium doped ceria as an effective barrier layer in solid oxide electrochemical cells

Sentencas: The NDC50 barrier layer has significantly decreased polarization resistance across a wide temperature and pO(2) range compared to the GDC10 barrier layer.
Titulo: Heavily neodymium doped ceria as an effective barrier layer in solid oxide electrochemical cells

Sentencas: The rare earth C-type structure of the NDC50 barrier layer causes barrier free migration of oxygen ions resulting in improved ionic conductivity compared to GDC10.
Titulo: Heavily neodymium doped ceria as an effective barrier layer in solid oxide electrochemical cells

Sentencas: Distribution of relaxation time (DRT) modeling has been used to obtain insights into the electrode processes.
Titulo: Heavily neodymium doped ceria as an effective barrier layer in solid oxide electrochemical cells
